course_metadata.title: Advanced digital technologies in post-disaster/conflict housing reconstruction for circularity

content_chunks.content: This course teaches students and professionals about new digital tools that can help rebuild homes and buildings after disasters or conflicts, while also being environmentally friendly. We'll look at how the construction industry can reuse materials and reduce waste, which is called the 'circular economy.' We'll explore several new technologies like: Digital Twins and Building Information Modelling (BIM), Geographic Information System (GIS), Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Data-Analytics, Internet of Things (IoT), Blockchain. These tools can help make rebuilding projects more efficient and sustainable. The course combines theory with real-world examples to show both the challenges and opportunities in rebuilding after disasters. We'll focus on how these new technologies can help use resources better, reuse materials, cut down on waste, and build stronger communities. By the end of the course, you'll know how to use these digital tools in your own rebuilding projects. This knowledge will help you work in more sustainable ways and contribute to creating buildings and communities that are better for the environment.

Digital technology for sustainable post-disaster reconstruction - this course delivers advanced digital tools for circular economy applications in rebuilding scenarios. Technology for material tracking and reuse includes Building Information Modelling (BIM) and Digital Twins for resource optimization, while Geographic Information System (GIS) enables damage assessment and resource management. The course integrates Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) and Large Language Models (LLM) for enhanced decision-making, alongside Artificial Intelligence for predictive analytics and collaborative AI agents systems. Internet of Things (IoT) sensors provide smart building monitoring capabilities, while blockchain technology ensures material passports and supply chain transparency. Participants gain expertise in circular economy principles, material reuse strategies, digital ecosystem integration, and API integration for comprehensive reconstruction management. The curriculum prepares professionals for technology adoption challenges and equips them with skills to implement circular construction practices using advanced digital technologies.

content_chunks.title: Introduction to Circular Economy in Post-Disaster Reconstruction - Principles of circular economy in construction, Challenges in post-disaster/conflict scenarios
Overview of Digital Technologies for Circular Reconstruction - Overview of relevant technologies, existing and potential use cases
Building Information Modelling (BIM) and Digital Twins for Circular Reconstruction (Intermediate) - BIM basics and applications in post-disaster contexts, Material tracking and reuse through BIM
Preparation for workshop – Basic instructions for interpreting BIM models
Overview of LLM applications involving Retrieval Augmented Generation
Hands-On workshop – Data visualisation and retrieval augmented generation using LLMs
GIS for data visualization and interpretation - damage assessment, resource management, asset tracking
Preparation for workshop – Basic instructions handling geospatial data
Hands-On workshop – data visualization and decision support using GIS

Artificial Intelligence and Big Data Analytics (Intermediate) - AI applications in circular construction practices, Predictive analytics for resource optimization, Independent and collaborative AI agents.
Preparation for workshop – Basic instructions for programming AI Agents
Hands-On workshop – Specialized and Collaborate AI Agents
Internet of Things (IoT) and Smart Buildings (Intermediate) - IoT sensors for building performance monitoring, Smart systems for resource management
Blockchain and Material Passports (Advanced) - Implementing material passports for circularity, Supply chain transparency in reconstruction
Preparation for workshop – Basic instructions for handling Blockchain
Hands-On workshop – Tracking and updating data in a Blockchain
Integrating Digital Technologies for Circular Reconstruction (Intermediate) - Creating a digital ecosystem for circular practices, Overcoming challenges in technology adoption
Preparation for workshop – Cast study with instruction on integrating various APIs for technology integration
Hands-On workshop – Using multiple technologies along with collaborative AI Agents for decision making
Future Trends in Digital Technologies for Circular Reconstruction (Basic) - Emerging technologies and their potential impact, Preparing for future developments
